ent felipe calderón however while the opening provided an occasion the real cause for celebration was the range of benefits and opportunities that goldcorps peñasquito mine will create for the people of the region to date goldcorp has invested cdn  billion in the areas economic growth on both a direct and indirect basis this has led to the creation of more than  jobs most of which will go to people in the mazapil district goldcorps investment has also resulted in the development of medical clinics community amenities a water purification plant houses schools and training for teachers as president calderón noted through peñasquito goldcorp has established a path to progress for the area goldcorp is also working to support and empower people and groups including women single mothers and the elderly who are all too often left behind even during times of prosperity goldcorp is committed to making a sustainable contribution to the zacatecas region weve learned through experience that supporting the communities near our operations is not only the right thing to do its the smart thing to do it is an essential step in creating value and opportunity for all of our stakeholders annual decant closing ceremony at musselwhite october   as a form of giving thanks and respect to the land and the water that surrounds us representatives from the local first nation communities visit the mine site every year to perform a religious ceremony and bless the water prior to releasing it through the treatment wetland and into the natural environment musselwhite is located within traditional first nations territory each year in early summer elders and other representatives from local first nations communities come to musselwhite for the annual decant opening ceremony this years ceremony took place on june   the elders perform a blessing on the water used in our operations after the blessing the water is released into our treatment wetland there it is naturally purified before re–entering the larger environmental system in early fall the elders and other community members return to mark the annual decant closing and another successful year of effluent release with a ceremony of thanksgiving at the end of the ceremony local first nations youth close the decant valve stopping the flow of effluent into the treatment wetland until next years opening ceremony these annual ceremonies remind us of the value and importance of a healthy environment they also strengthen our partnerships with local first nations communities emphasize our shared commitment to environmental responsibility and highlight potential career opportunities at the mine that are available to first nations youth contact us goldcorp inc head office park place suite  burrard street vancouver bc  vc x telephone   facsimile   toronto office  –  adelaide street west toronto ontario canada  mh p telephone   facsimile   corporate report gri index global compact downloads contact us    print basket overview our company ceo message vision and mission awards about this report gri content performance data strategy and governance board of directors executive compensation business conduct key impacts risks and opportunities commitment to external initiatives economic contributions management approach corporate performance expenditures local economic impact economic initiatives workplace and ourpeople management approach our workforce safety health training and education labourmgmt relations diversity and equal opportunity emergency response workplace initiatives safety and health management approach joint safety and health committees safety health emergency response human rights management approach human rights human rights case studies community relations management approach stakeholder engagement community contributions indigenous relationships resettlement issues and concerns community initiatives environmental stewardship management approach materials energy greenhouse gas and air emissions implications of climate change effluents and waste water biodiversity transport product responsibility mine closure compliance environmental expenditure environmental case studies mm  pr  pr  pr  pr  pr  pr  pr  pr  pr  en  en world gold council home » corporate report » environmental stewardship » product responsibility product responsibility print page add to basket materials stewardship  product handling  lead and zinc concentrate goldcorp mines gold and silverbearing ore processes the ore and produces doré bars which are unrefined gold and silver bullion bars the doré bars are then transferred by secure means to precious metals refineries to be further processed into almostpure metal gold and silver doré bars pose no environmental or health risks and they can be disposed of in this form without environmental or social impacts as such we have not developed detailed protocols or procedures relating to product responsibility other than for product security and there were no instances of noncompliance with regulations or voluntary codes concerning the health and safety impacts of our products in  materials stewardship gold is used as bullion and in jewellery glass and electronics with jewellery consuming about  of all gold produced silver is valued as a precious metal and its halide salts especially silver nitrate are also widely used in photography the major outlets for silver are photography the electrical and electronic industries and domestic use as cutlery jewellery and mirrors both gold and silver are extensively recycled mining accounts for about twothirds of the global supply of gold the other third comes from existing supplies – mainly recycled scrap gold eg from jewellery dental materials plating solutions and electronic equipment and gold from central banks photographic wastes spent catalysts and electronic scrap are the major sources of materials for silver recycling product handling goldcorp sells into the worldwide gold and silver market and as a result is not dependent on a particular purchaser we sell our products to refineries or smelters for secondary treatment – not directly to the public we have a commercial relationship with our customers and any issues that may arise are addressed according to the terms of our mutual contractual obligations there were no complaints incidences of breaches of customer privacy or losses of customer data in  we are unaware of any outstanding customer issues the doré bars produced at the mine site do not carry public labelling they are transferred to a refinery for further processing to the london bullion market lbm standard once produced all  gold bars are allocated a bar number and imprinted with an lbm registered refiners mark there were no instances of noncompliance with regulations or voluntary codes concerning product information and the labelling of our products in  there are no codes or voluntary standards that relate to marketing communications regarding gold andor silver doré bars goldcorp is a member of the world gold council as the gold industrys key marketing body the world gold council works closely with jewellery retailers manufacturers wholesalers banks investment companies and distribution specialists to promote the use of gold in jewellery and industrial applications as well as by central banks and other official sector institutions there were no instances of noncompliance with regulations or voluntary codes concerning marketing communications in  there were no fines for noncompliance with laws and regulations concerning the provision and use of our products in  lead and zinc concentrate with the development of the peñasquito mine in mexico goldcorp has added lead and zinc concentrates to its product mix trial shipments of concentrate commenced at the end of  and continued through  peñasquito completed commissioning and achieved commercial production on september   while lead has been mined and used in industrial and household products for centuries and zinc is a trace element essential to human health both pose risks to human health and the environment when not managed correctly concentrates containing combinations of gold silver lead and zinc are loaded onto highway road vehicles for transport to incountry smelters or to sea ports for export to foreign smelters in asia europe and north america transportation of such concentrate is subject to numerous risks including but not limited to road blocks terrorism weather conditions and environmental liabilities in the event of an accident or leak peñasquito has developed emergency response plans to cover the trucking of its concentrate goldcorp does not produce lead or zinc products that are sold directly to the public goldcorp  wikipedia goldcorp from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search goldcorp inc type public traded as tsx g nyse gg sptsx  component industry gold mining founded   years ago  headquarters vancouver british columbia canada key people david garofalo ceo ian telfer chairman of the board and director products gold revenue  million  operating income  million  net income  million  total assets  billion  number of employees   website goldcorpcom goldcorp inc is a gold production company headquartered in vancouver british columbia canada the company employs about  people worldwide engaged in gold mining and related activities including exploration extraction processing and reclamation goldcorp’s operating assets include four mines in canada two mines in mexico and four in central and south americacitation needed as of the third quarter of  goldcorp was the worlds fourthlargest producer of gold in june  goldcorp was named one of corporate knights magazines best  corporate citizens in canada in the same year the company was also ranked among canadas top  employers goldcorp has repeatedly been accused of harming the environment livestock and public health in multiple studies by advocacy groups and activists contaminating areas with toxic heavy metals by its mining activities these allegations have been refuted by the company and none of these allegations have been proved in a court of law the companys track record around transparency policies and practices has improved since a damning  study accused the company of human rights violations contents  operations  operations map  legend  financial        history  environmental impact  san martin mine honduras  marlin mine guatemala  pueblo viejo mining project dominican republic  see also  references operationsedit operations mapedit goldcorp’s operating assets include four mines in canada one mine in mexico and four in central and south america goldcorp also has a number of projects including the coffee cochenour and borden projects in canada and nuevaunión formerly known as project corridor   interest in chilecitation needed legendedit red lake mine canada porcupine mine canada musselwhite mine canada éléonore mine canada peñasquito mine mexico cerro negro mine argentina marlin mine guatemala pueblo viejo mine dominican republic   ownership alumbrera mine argentina   ownership coffee project canada cochenour project canada borden project canada nuevaunión project chile   ownership in  goldcorp announced it had formed a  joint venture with barrick gold to consolidate the maricunga gold belt in the atacama region of northern chile goldcorp acquired the minority  interest held by kinross gold in cerro casale and  interest in the quebrada seca exploration project for us million and a  royalty interest in favor of kinross on  of gross revenues from payable metal from cerro casale and quebrada seca with kinross foregoing the first  million payable a contingent payment of  million payable after a construction decision at cerro casale and assumption of a  million obligation to barrick payable on commercial production at cerro casale  in april  goldcorp closed on the sale of its los filos gold mine guerrero state mexico to leagold mining for us million the transaction included us million in cash and  million in common shares of leadgold goldcorp also nominated russell ball the leagolds board of directors  in june  goldcorp announced it had formed a a  joint venture with barrick gold to develop the maricunga district in chile  the transaction included the acquisition of exeter resource corp along with a us million payment at closing to kinross gold goldcorp also granted kinross a  royalty on the cerro casale and quebrada seca deposits  financialedit edit in q  goldcorp reported net earnings of us million and production of  ounces of gold  in q  goldcorp reported net earnings of us million and production of  ounces of gold  edit in  goldcorp produced  million ounces of gold at allin sustaining costs of  per ounce  edit  production totaled  ounces for the fourth quarter and  ounces for the full year citation needed compared to  ounces and  ounces respectively in citation needed financials us  millions   revenues   adjusted net earnings   cash flow from operations   cash  cash equivalents   total assets at dec    citation needed historyedit goldcorp was officially incorporated in  following a period of ma activity the company quickly grew to become a leading gold producer the company is focused on responsible mining practices with safe lowcost production in areas of low political risk through the consistent application of its business strategy goldcorp has achieved significant growth industry recognition and numerous awards in  goldcorp founder rob mcewen launched the goldcorp challenge sharing with the public the company’s geological data with the offer of  in prizes to those who could help locate red lake mine’s next six million ounces of gold the challenge was successful with more than  sites identified and more than  per cent of sites yielding significant gold reserves the challenge helped turn the company from a struggling enterprise into one of the most profitable in the industry in january  goldcorp announced it had divested two noncore assets through the sales of the cerro blanco gold project in guatemala to bluestone resources as well as the los filos mine in mexico to leagold mining in january  goldcorp reported preliminary full year  production totaling  million ounces of gold at allin sustaining costs of around  per ounce the company expects to increase total annual gold production by over  over the next five years to more than three million ounces annually in february  goldcorp announced it had purchased new golds  gold stream on the el morro deposit the el morro deposit is part of nuevaunión a  joint venture with teck resources that combines the relincho and el morro deposits  environmental impactedit goldcorp has been working to improve its approach to environmental stewardship the company publicly reports on its environmental performance on an annual basis and has been a member of the international council on mining and metals icmm since  the company’s el sauzal mine in mexico was also the first mine in the world to be successfully decommissioned in accordance with the international cyanide management code “icmc” despite this the environmental economic and human impact of the company’s latin american mines has been a controversial topic for a number of years san martin mine hondurasedit a study by italian activist flaviano bianchini in  found dangerous levels of arsenic and lead in the blood of hondurans living downstream from goldcorps san martin mine located in the siria valley while people living in the valley had equated their health problems with the mines operations since it opened in  both the company and the honduran government disputed the studys findings honduran authorities the company said took water samples during three visits in  and all ph measurements were normal they also reviewed and approved the mines closure plan in  two studies commissioned by the ukbased advocacy group cafod have found the companys methods to extract gold from lowgrade deposits also releases other toxic heavy metals such as arsenic mercury and lead contaminating streams and groundwater the first study from newcastle university detected acidic mine drainage whereby sulphides in the rock are exposed to oxygen and water and produce sulphuric acid which can have devastating effects on animals and plants a followup study by the same university found evidence of severe contamination in the form of highly acidic and metalrich water from the mine site flowing into a stream used by villagers for agriculture and domestic purposes since the closure of san martin mine in  the  hectare former mine site has been reclaimed into agricultural farmland and the former camp facilities remodeled into an ecotourism hotel these developments have since provided employment skills training and new investment to the area marlin mine guatemalaedit an investigative report by the ctv television networks w published on their website on april   reported criticism by human rights workers about the damage they believe mining companies were doing to the people the land and the culture of guatemala the same news program ran a fourpart documentary entitled paradise lost which explored some of the controversy surrounding goldcorps marlin mine operation and investigated the economic environmental and social costs and benefits of canadian mining operations in central america at the request of goldcorp shareholders an independent human rights impact assessment hria was conducted by external auditors in  goldcorp has since implemented all recommendations from the hira including the publishing of an official human rights policy in  on july –  the selforganized international peoples’ health tribunal a panel of twelve judges with backgrounds in science health ecology and human rights met in guatemala to hear testimony relating to the effects of goldcorps south american mines after the twoday tribunal the panel found goldcorp financially liable for health and ecological damages to the communities near its mines in honduras guatemala and mexico as a self organized tribunal the panel findings carry no legal bearing however the company did voluntarily secure financial bonds to ensure responsible closure the marlin mine has since been lauded as a model of responsible mine closure and was named one of the  most socially responsible companies in central america by el economista the economist magazine pueblo viejo mining project dominican republicedit pueblo viejo mining project takes place in the dominican republic and is operated by barrick pueblo viejo a firm owned by barrick gold and goldcorp  years of operation are scheduled for this project which is likely to raise the exports of the dominican republic clearly the project is accused of having caused contamination and illegal logging the illegal logging has since been attributed to local village people in  barrick gold opened a water treatment plant that has since successfully rehabilitated the contaminated area see alsoedit companies portal gold as an investment gold mining referencesedit  a b c goldcorp financial data annual data retrieved october     top  companies  forbes october     company profile for goldcorp inc gg retrieved january     goldcorp  our workforce goldcorpcom   simon walker gold new fundamentals engineering  mining journal feb  v n p   best  results  corporate knights  retrieved    goldcorp inc  dispelling the myths of marlin wwwgoldcorpcom retrieved    goldcorp inc overall winner in  for excellence in corporate reporting wwwcpacanadaca retrieved    goldcorp and barrick gold to consolidate cerro casale and caspiche gold projects in  joint venture wwwjuniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    leagold mining completes acquisition of los filos gold mine wwwjuniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    goldcorp completes  joint venture formation with barrick gold to develop maricunga district chile wwwjuniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    kinross gold completes sale of cerro casale interest wwwjuniorminingnetworkcom retri