th teck resources that combines the relincho and el morro deposits  environmental impactedit goldcorp has been working to improve its approach to environmental stewardship the company publicly reports on its environmental performance on an annual basis and has been a member of the international council on mining and metals icmm since  the company’s el sauzal mine in mexico was also the first mine in the world to be successfully decommissioned in accordance with the international cyanide management code “icmc” despite this the environmental economic and human impact of the company’s latin american mines has been a controversial topic for a number of years san martin mine hondurasedit a study by italian activist flaviano bianchini in  found dangerous levels of arsenic and lead in the blood of hondurans living downstream from goldcorps san martin mine located in the siria valley while people living in the valley had equated their health problems with the mines operations since it opened in  both the company and the honduran government disputed the studys findings honduran authorities the company said took water samples during three visits in  and all ph measurements were normal they also reviewed and approved the mines closure plan in  two studies commissioned by the ukbased advocacy group cafod have found the companys methods to extract gold from lowgrade deposits also releases other toxic heavy metals such as arsenic mercury and lead contaminating streams and groundwater the first study from newcastle university detected acidic mine drainage whereby sulphides in the rock are exposed to oxygen and water and produce sulphuric acid which can have devastating effects on animals and plants a followup study by the same university found evidence of severe contamination in the form of highly acidic and metalrich water from the mine site flowing into a stream used by villagers for agriculture and domestic purposes since the closure of san martin mine in  the  hectare former mine site has been reclaimed into agricultural farmland and the former camp facilities remodeled into an ecotourism hotel these developments have since provided employment skills training and new investment to the area marlin mine guatemalaedit an investigative report by the ctv television networks w published on their website on april   reported criticism by human rights workers about the damage they believe mining companies were doing to the people the land and the culture of guatemala the same news program ran a fourpart documentary entitled paradise lost which explored some of the controversy surrounding goldcorps marlin mine operation and investigated the economic environmental and social costs and benefits of canadian mining operations in central america at the request of goldcorp shareholders an independent human rights impact assessment hria was conducted by external auditors in  goldcorp has since implemented all recommendations from the hira including the publishing of an official human rights policy in  on july –  the selforganized international peoples’ health tribunal a panel of twelve judges with backgrounds in science health ecology and human rights met in guatemala to hear testimony relating to the effects of goldcorps south american mines after the twoday tribunal the panel found goldcorp financially liable for health and ecological damages to the communities near its mines in honduras guatemala and mexico as a self organized tribunal the panel findings carry no legal bearing however the company did voluntarily secure financial bonds to ensure responsible closure the marlin mine has since been lauded as a model of responsible mine closure and was named one of the  most socially responsible companies in central america by el economista the economist magazine pueblo viejo mining project dominican republicedit pueblo viejo mining project takes place in the dominican republic and is operated by barrick pueblo viejo a firm owned by barrick gold and goldcorp  years of operation are scheduled for this project which is likely to raise the exports of the dominican republic clearly the project is accused of having caused contamination and illegal logging the illegal logging has since been attributed to local village people in  barrick gold opened a water treatment plant that has since successfully rehabilitated the contaminated area see alsoedit companies portal gold as an investment gold mining referencesedit  a b c goldcorp financial data annual data retrieved october     top  companies  forbes october     company profile for goldcorp inc gg retrieved january     goldcorp  our workforce goldcorpcom   simon walker gold new fundamentals engineering  mining journal feb  v n p   best  results  corporate knights  retrieved    goldcorp inc  dispelling the myths of marlin wwwgoldcorpcom retrieved    goldcorp inc overall winner in  for excellence in corporate reporting wwwcpacanadaca retrieved    goldcorp and barrick gold to consolidate cerro casale and caspiche gold projects in  joint venture wwwjuniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    leagold mining completes acquisition of los filos gold mine wwwjuniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    goldcorp completes  joint venture formation with barrick gold to develop maricunga district chile wwwjuniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    kinross gold completes sale of cerro casale interest wwwjuniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    goldcorp produces  ounces of gold in q  wwwjuniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    goldcorp reports q net earnings of us million wwwjuniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    goldcorp reports fourth quarter and full year  results juniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    bluestone resources to acquire cerro blanco gold project from goldcorp inc juniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    goldcorp announces sale of los filos mine juniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    goldcorp reports preliminary q and full year  production results totaling  million ounces juniorminingnetworkcom retrieved    goldcorp annou